According to information, the members were conducting their highway patrols on the Hendrina/Bethal road when they spotted a suspicious Toyota Hilux bakkie. They then stopped and searched the said vehicle and discovered bags of dagga weighting at 230 kg.  The suspect was immediately arrested for dealing with dagga. The Provincial Commissioner of SAPS in Mpumalanga Lieutenant General Semakaleng Daphney Manamela has applauded the members for their vigilance during patrols and encouraged them to continue working hard.